rComments: Dr. Waheed Hussain is one of the best professors I've had at UTSC. If you're serious about getting a good mark, he will take time to help you as much as you want. He will challenge your thoughts and will make you think beyond your limits. He is a very fair marker so if you're dedicated enough, you will receive a good mark.

Oh man, such an amazing prof! He will listen to you, challenge your thoughts, and makes you think beyond your limits. He is the definition of a good philosophy prof. Definitely recommend those who are interested in political philosophy to take his course.

Clearly enthusiastic and easy to listen to. I really enjoyed his class, wish he was less involved what the students opinions on everything was though. He took up a lot of lecture time answering questions- which is what tutorials are for. But overall a sweet and easy credit.

Decent class, good lecturer (clear voice, eye contact) however I didn't enjoy lectures   I found that it was too much discussion and not enough actual "lecturing"   Midterm was brutal (Although it was his first time teaching, yes, I would say you  have to work for it)    Nice guy.
Fully engages 500 students with ease. There is no text book and class discussions are amassing.
His class was absolutely amazing! I recommend taking any course he runs. Super engaging.
